{
  "text": "Cell-free Phagosome/Lysosome Docking Assay Phagosome/lysosome interactions were studied with a cellfree scintillation proximity assay consisting of tritium-labeled donor membranes, phagosome acceptors containing scintillant latex beads, cytosol, and nucleoside triphosphates. In this assay light emission results when \u2424 particles are absorbed by scintillant beads. Because of the short range of tritiumderived \u2424 radiation and because of geometric constraints, scintillation can only be elicited by labeled vesicles that are in close vicinity (within \u03f3600 nm) of the scintillant [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "32373167",
    "[CITATION_2]": "25440557"
